### ClinIntelAI API Testing
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@email = doctor@example.com
@password = password123

### 1. Register a new doctor
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Dr. John Smith",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 2. Login (use credentials from register or existing user)
# @name login
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/[...nextauth]
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###  3. Get all patients (requires authentication)
GET {{baseUrl}}/patients
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Create a new patient
POST {{baseUrl}}/patients
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane.doe@example.com",
  "phone": "+1-555-123-4567",
  "dateOfBirth": "1985-03-15",
  "gender": "FEMALE",
  "medicalRecordNumber": "MRN-12345",
  "notes": "Patient has history of diabetes"
}

### 5. Get a specific patient
@patientId = PATIENT_ID_HERE
GET {{baseUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

### 6. Update a patient
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Jane Doe Updated",
  "notes": "Updated patient information"
}

### 7. Get all files
GET {{baseUrl}}/files
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

### 8. Get all files for a specific patient
GET {{baseUrl}}/files?patientId={{patientId}}
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

### 9. Upload a file (Note: Use form-data, this is just a template)
# For file upload, use the UI or a tool like Postman/Insomnia
POST {{baseUrl}}/files
Content-Type: multipart/form-data
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

# FormData:
# - file: [your file]
# - patientId: {{patientId}}

### 10. Get a specific file
@fileId = FILE_ID_HERE
GET {{baseUrl}}/files/{{fileId}}
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

### 11. Analyze a file
POST {{baseUrl}}/analyze
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "fileId": "{{fileId}}",
  "inferenceType": "csv-analysis",
  "inputData": {
    "columns": ["column1", "column2"]
  }
}

### 12. Get all inferences
GET {{baseUrl}}/analyze
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

### 13. Get inferences for a specific patient
GET {{baseUrl}}/analyze?patientId={{patientId}}
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

### 14. Get inferences for a specific file
GET {{baseUrl}}/analyze?fileId={{fileId}}
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

### 15. Delete a patient
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

### 16. Delete a file
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/files/{{fileId}}
Cookie: next-auth.session-token=YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE

###
### NOTES:
### - Replace YOUR_SESSION_TOKEN_HERE with actual session token from browser cookies
### - Replace PATIENT_ID_HERE and FILE_ID_HERE with actual IDs from responses
### - For better testing, use the UI at http://localhost:3000
###
